      "animation": "double_jump_salto",
      "filename": "double_jump_salto_000.png through double_jump_salto_005.png",
      "source_sheet": "chatgpt_salto_board_v2",
      "note": "6-frame continuous forward somersault (launch / quarter rotation / full inversion / three-quarter rotation / opening up / landing-ready), replacing a prior 3-frame version whose first and last frames looked nearly identical (read as a bounce, not a flip) -- also brings the pack in line with DOUBLE_JUMP_POSE_FRAMES's comment in config.py, which already expected 6 frames @ 16fps. Generated by ChatGPT from a 3x2 green-screen reference board (referencing the pack's own prior salto frames and jump_000 for style/scale, with an explicit instruction to keep one consistent rotation direction and make each panel visibly distinct). Chroma-keyed and re-composited onto the standard 256x256 canvas using a single fixed scale factor (derived from frame 0's tucked-launch pose matched to the old frame 0's composited height of 189px, for visual continuity with the preceding single jump), centered at x=128 and top-anchored at y=36 -- matching the original 3-frame version's own convention of a fixed top position rather than a feet-at-anchor.y position, since mid-flip poses have no ground contact and a fixed top reads more stably than a varying bottom during the tuck/extend of a flip.",
      "clipped": false
    },
