    {
      "set": "selected_46",
      "animation": "dash",
      "filename": "dash_000.png through dash_003.png",
      "source_sheet": "chatgpt_dash_board_v1",
      "note": "4-frame explosive forward dash burst (launch / full low horizontal extension / recovery drive / settle back to standing guard), generated by ChatGPT from a 4x1 green-screen reference board (referencing the pack's own idle/walk/block_mid/kick_mid for costume and proportions). This animation did not exist before in HD/LD; dash previously fell back to the walk cycle (see assets/fighters/CONTRACT.md). Chroma-keyed and re-composited onto the standard 256x256 canvas using a single fixed scale factor derived from panel 4 (the standing settle pose) matched to the pack's standard standing height (197px, from idle_000); panels 1-3 keep that same scale applied to their own bbox, so their shorter raw height reads as a real low forward lean rather than a scale error. Feet stay at anchor y=214, centered at x=128. fps=24 with loop=false so the 4 frames play once over ~0.167s, matching DASH_DURATION_FRAMES/FPS in config.py.",
      "clipped": false
    },
    {
      "set": "selected_46",
      "animation": "block_low",
      "filename": "block_low_000.png",
      "source_sheet": "chatgpt_block_fix_board_v1",
      "note": "Crouching low-guard, replacing the prior single 'crouch_block' frame which showed her kneeling on one knee with a fist near her face -- a resting/defeated pose, not an active low guard, and which was also never actually rendered in-game because the key 'crouch_block' didn't match what Renderer.animation_key() looks up while crouched and blocking (f'block_{{fighter.block_level}}' -> 'block_low'; see CONTRACT.md). A first replacement (2-frame idle loop) fixed the kneeling issue (both feet planted, matching crouch_idle) but playtest feedback found the arms still read as hanging down near the knees rather than actively blocking; regenerated a second time with both forearms angled up and forward to form a shield in front of the torso/hips, and simplified back to a single frame (matching block_mid/block_high's convention) since the second corrective pass only produced one pose. Chroma-keyed and re-composited onto the standard 256x256 canvas using a fixed scale matched to crouch_idle_000's composited height (111px, same crouch-depth category); feet stay at anchor y=214, centered at x=128. Note: the raw chroma-keyed source had a stray opaque border pixel within ~4px of the edge that skewed an initial bbox measurement (minX/minY landed exactly on the margin boundary) -- resolved by widening the bbox-scan margin to 10px, see the pitfall documented in HOW_TO_GENERATE_IMAGES.md.",
      "clipped": false
    }
